            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "School till 10th standard isn't often a very important part of our lives or atleast that's what we all think but now on looking back at my school when I'm doing my engineering i often thank those buildings and pay my utmost respect to the teachers who showed me at my core who instilled in me the qualities that are quite well known but really hard to find.... I even today remember in 1st standard i had mrs.Abhijata Chavan as my class teacher and she punished me and made me stand in the classroom, lunch break came between the two periods but I didn't sit down until she came again in class, Abhijata ma'am hugged me and cried that day and said that she'll never do this to me again and that I'm her favourite student. That's really enough to make a grown man cry.... This is one story and there are innumerous stories that still can be listened in the quadrangle... Anjali tr, Durga tr, Pallavi tr, Philomena ma'am , Vidya ma'am , Manjusha ma'am all shall have a place in my heart forever....",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
